JC Flowers & Co. LLC is in talks
with Spanish savings bank  Caja de Ahorros del Mediterraneo (CAM) , or
CAM, to buy a stake for between 400 million euros ($571 million)
and 1 billion euros,  Expansion  reported, without saying how it
obtained the information.  JC Flowers wants the state to be a guarantor for up to 2
billion euros of losses as a condition, Expansion says.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angeline Benoit in Madrid at 
 abenoit4@bloomberg.net  